On many previous occassions, I would show people how to upgrade their debians boxes. First I would su to root. This is not good practice. Use sudo instead, and use your user password.

Example: 
 sudo dselect update

Update package listings, and then upgrade :)

 sudo apt-get -u dist-upgrade
